One person has been hacked down on Saturday afternoon during a cult clash in Osogbo, Osun State. DAILY POST learnt that some cultist cashed the man to Isale-Osun area and was consequently apprehended at Laro Primary School, workers drive area in Osogbo. It was gathered that the incident occurred around 2:30 to 3 pm on Saturday. Residents to this medium that the unidentified man was hacked several times before he was shot dead. The remain of the man was later taken by Oâ€™Ambulance and deposited at the morgue in Asubiaro General Hospital, Osogbo. The Public Relations Officer of Osun State Command, Yemisi Opalola confirmed the incident. She noted that the command was on top of the matter and has opened an investigation on it.